@exgenesis I guess you are doing something like this?:
1. Get all people you interacted with on a given timeframe. call it neighbors.
2. For all neighbors, get their interactions with any other neighbors on that same time timeframe.

@exgenesis 3. Build a graph where each person is a node and each interaction is an edge.
4. Create a 2D layout for the graph (curious on what you chose for this).
5. Bundle edges with kdeeb.

